           throws Exception
        Decodes FAST FIX message into byte array and returns the size of the output array.
        Parameters:
        encodedMessage - the FAST FIX encoded message
        encodedMessageLength - the number of elements filled in the encodedMessage array
        decodedMessage - the decoded message
        Returns:
        the number of bytes filled in the decodedMessage array
        Throws:
        Exception - if there is a problem decoding.

      • setSpy

        public void setSpy(ISpy spy)
        Set a spy if you want to analyse the decoding process.

        Typical use would be to create a spy, then set it on this FastBytesDecoder using this method, then do the decoding and display the spy. For example: FastBytesDecoder decoder = new FastBytesDecoder( fastContext ); Spy spy = new Spy(); decoder.setSpy( spy ); decoder.decode( encodedMessage, encodedMessagelength, decodedMessage ); System.out.println( spy );

        Parameters:
        spy - Spy to use. Can be null, in which case spying is turned off.
